        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I'm replying now, mostly to get my # of posts up ;-) so all this info may be a little wrong. The 'kiting' doesn't work well until level 12. You will be outta mana very fast trying this at low levels. Right now, when you have just one enemy, send pet, watch his health (/pet health) and go in when he gets low. When 2 or more enemies, fear then darkness one, then kill the remaining, then kill other when it comes back. Now if you are in tight place where one enemy can run and bring friends, it’s good to darkness him so he runs slow. In Warrens darkness helps a lot but it’s not fool proof.</P><P>Yes you want to keep spell skils up, but at low levels it's a juggling act between spells HP and mana.</P><P>The level 4 spells were nice, level 8 spells were very mana expensive at first. Plus it’s good to do some of your own fighting now, to get defense and other skills up. You don’t want to be practicing them when you are facing higher level mobs.</P><P>My 2cp.<BR>Renovo<BR>Druzil Ro</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
