        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         The first undead fear is Spook the Dead at lvl 8 I think.  It uses a lot less mana than regular fear.  I really didnt start fear kiting mush until the high teens.  Mostly, I used the send in the pet, DoT, tank when pet low method.  <BR>Always keep dark pact up when fight, but watch your heath.  Tap when low.  You really don't get a good nuke for non-undead until 24, so you can use your life tap until then.  When you are full mana though, a pure nuke is more efficient.  Against undead you get Ward undead earlier (lvl 8 I think).  When DoTing, becarefull how many you hit the mob with.  Too many DoTs (3 or 4) will cause the MoB to agro you instead of pet.  <BR>A necromancer can usually solo yellows and maybe a low red.  You are usally better at this at the level you get a new pet and then the ability decreases as the pet ages until you get your next pet.  Yellow and reds will resist your spells more though.</P><P>Suetekh<BR>Necromancer of 24 Reanimations<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
