        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         We got fear at lvl 4?  Don't don't remember fear kiting till like lvl 14 or so in Oasis.  Probably cause it used so much mana at lower lvls.  I think I just used it to split spawns.</P><P>Kite = Snare mob, DoT mob, run like hell, nuke mob (maybe)<BR>Fear Kite = Snare mob, Pet on mob, fear mob, DoT mob, nuke mob (maybe)<BR>Reverse Kite = Fear kite (It's the reverse of what 90% of people in EQ know as kiting)<BR>Root Rott = Snare mob, root mob, dot mob, take nap, send pet when mob breaks free or gets low on health (jsut to speed things up and to use less mana)</P><P>Something that took me a while to figure out.  A necros life is a balancing act between HPs and mana.  It is a great big circle.  you drain HPs to get mana, use mana to get HPs, and in the process kill the mob and get exp.  Once you get the HP to mana spells, learn to keep them up the whole time you are fighting.  You will have tons more mana at your disposal than anyone around you.  If you do things right fear kiting and with pet you can kill continuously without ever stopping.  Pretty close anyway.  I can kill for about an hour before I have to take a break right now at lvl 52.  This is with about 30 seconds between mobs and that is just to check buffs, pet HPs, and find a new mob.</P><P>-DV</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
